    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-17T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–1754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-17T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 17, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 466. Repeated information Ottawa 9,
                    London 299, Tokyo 147, Bogota 6, Paris 453, Bangkok 28, Seoul 134. Re <gloss
                        target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 454.<note n="1" xml:id="d242fn1">Dated June
                        16. <ref target="#pg_388">p. 388</ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Drafting committee of 6 met today, June 17, and completed first working
                        draft report to <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>. Belgian, Ethiopian,
                        Netherlands, Philippine <pb facs="0418" n="392" xml:id="pg_392"/>
                        representatives also present. <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> delegate
                        out of town. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> will pouch draft<note
                            n="2" xml:id="d242fn2">Not printed.</note> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_MCRJG1">McClurkin</persName>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>Agreed to following procedure: <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>No further meeting in Geneva;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Working draft will be sent 6 respective governments for
                                    comments;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Representatives of 6 will then meet in Washington finish
                                    preparation of report;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                                <item>It will then be submitted to full committee of 15 and their
                                    governments for consideration and approval;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Completed report will be submitted to SYGUN at suitable time,
                                    i.e., 9th <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> session.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>Group felt this procedure might help keep 8th <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                                >GA</gloss> or special session Thailand resolution<note n="3"
                                xml:id="d242fn3">For related documentation, see <ref
                                    target="#pg_727">pp. 727</ref> ff.</note> from taking up Korean
                            question.</p>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Principal point today’s discussion was armistice agreement. All
                        representatives expressed considerable concern over <persName
                            corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName>’s press remarks Wednesday on
                        invalidation armistice. Owing to these remarks, <persName corresp="#p_UHF1"
                            >Urrutia</persName> (Colombia) proposed and others supported adding
                        General <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName>’s statement in 15th
                        plenary (<gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 450<note n="4"
                            xml:id="d242fn4">Not printed, but see <ref target="#pg_379">footnote 6,
                                p. 379</ref>.</note>) to report itself. They all stressed important
                        report contains some reference to continued validity and effect of armistice
                        agreement. <persName corresp="#p_YKT1">Young</persName> reported briefly on
                            <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName>’s explanation and
                        circumstances underlying his remarks (<gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                            >Secto</gloss> 464<note n="5" xml:id="d242fn5">
                            <ref target="#d241">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                            </ref>.</note>) which had been made sharper in press versions than he
                        had apparently intended. However, <persName corresp="#p_YKT1"
                            >Young</persName> suggested and group agreed possible addition <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName>’s statement or short reference to
                        armistice should be referred to delegations or governments, because it
                        involved several important matters, before being incorporated in working
                        draft at later stage.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Group also suggested ending report with hope expressed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> as chairman last plenary that day may
                        soon come when task of conference can be carried through to successful
                        conclusion. Agreed that this question, like one above, should be referred to
                        delegations or governments of six and taken up later by Washington working
                        group.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
